			<td width="44%"> Resumo
			<div style="text-align:justify;">
				<P>
					<B>Introdução</B>: Introduction: Labour Law was born with the purpose of ensuring human dignity to the worker, to suppress the vital condition it was in at the time of the Industrial Revolution. Three principles can be mentioned as general guidelines to the Labour Law, which are: human dignity, protecting the right to life and to physical and mental inviolability and non-discrimination; proportionality and reasonableness, prohibiting excesses of whatever form; and good faith, forbidding the abuse of rights.					<B>Objetivo</B>: the Federal Constitution provides, in article 7, item XXII, the employee´s right to safe working, hygienic and healthy, sheltered, the right to additional remuneration for strenuous, unhealthy or dangerous work, as provided in item XXIII, of the same article. Thus, this project aims to recognize cases where the employee can exercise the right of resistance, the forms prescribed by law for this to be used, discuss the foundation of the right to temporary stability be used only to the employee returning from leave per occupational disease or trauma and analyze the impact caused by the failure in health and labor security measures worker to business productivity.					<B>Metodologia</B>: developed a descriptive, analytical and critical study fundamentally linked to the reading and interpretation of the bibliographic material collected with the use of reading book reports to facilitate the concatenation of affairs at the time of externalizing research. Systematic doctrinal sources through reading workbooks and, after analysis and interpretation of all the selected material - doctrine, legislation, jurisprudence, information and extra-legal data - outside the written dissertation.					<B>Resultados</B>: 					<B>Conclusões</B>: it is concluded that the employer has the variandi ius, due to its power steering, which enables monitor and unilaterally change the employment contract, provided the employee is not injured, the limits being respected in their use and not violated essential elements of the employment relationship in order to meet the requirements of the company´s development, however, always observing the fundamental and constitutional guarantees. Thereby surpassing the employer limits his power, incurs abuse, giving birth to the employee´s right of revolution, which is a limit to the ius variandi, which does not identify with insubordination or indiscipline, since the employee is in full exercise of a right.				</P>
			</div><B>Palavras-chave</B>: Resistance. fundamental guarantees. jus variandi.			<BR>
